{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐλαφρ-ός</b>, ά, όν, <br /> and in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 5.20 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] ός, όν: (see. ἐλαχύς);— <b>light in weight</b>, τόν οἱ ἐ. ἔθηκε (i.e. λᾶαν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.450; ξύλου ἐλαφρότερα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.23; πῦρ 4th-5th c.BC: Parmenides Poeta Philosophus 8.57 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to βαρύς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 63c, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; in Epitaphs, γαῖαν ἔχοις ἐλαφράν '<b>sit tibi terra levis',</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" epigram Gr. 195 (from Vaxos), compare “Sammelb.” 315. \">Refs</a>] <i>adverb</i>, τά (i.e. δένδρεα)[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" οἱ πλώοιεν ἐλαφρῶς 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.240. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>light to bear, easy</b>, καί κεν ἐλαφρότερος πόλεμος Τρώεσσι γένοιτο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.287; συμφ ορὰν ἐλαφροτέραν καταστῆσαι 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 3.3.12; πόνος -ότερος ἑαυτοῦ συνηθείῃ γίνεται 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 241 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: later, <i>comparative</i> ἐλαφρώτερον ἄλγος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC(?): Maximus Astrologus 173 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; ἐλαφρόν [ἐστι] 'tis <b>light, easy</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 7.77, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 265, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>easy to understand</b>, [προβλήματα] ἐ. καὶ πιθανά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.133e, compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Dio Chrysostomus Sophista 18.11 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; ἐν ἐλαφρῷ ποιήσασθαί τι to make <b>light</b> of a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.154; οὐκ ἐν ἐ. ποιεῖσθαι [prev. author] 1.118 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐκ ἐν ἐ. no <b>light matter</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 22.212. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>] <i>adverb</i> -ρῶς, φέρειν ζυγόν to bear it <b>lightly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 2.93. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>light of digestion</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.137a. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>shallow</b>, διάπλους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Periplus Maris Rubri [1st c.AD]” 55; δῖναι [prev. work]40. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <i>active</i>, <b>ease-giving</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus “fragment” 8, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 2.92. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>light in moving, nimble</b>, γυῖα δ᾽ ἔθηκεν ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.122; ἦ μάλ᾽ ἐ. ἀνήρ 16.745; ἐλαφρότατος ποσσί 23.749 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χεῖρες.. ἐπαΐσσονται ἐ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\". [prev. work] 628; κίρκος.. ἐλαφρότατος πετεηνῶν 22.139, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.87; [ἵπποι] ἐλαφρότατοι θείειν 3.370; ἐλαφραῖς πτερύγων ῥιπαῖς 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 125 (_anapaest meter_); ἐ. ποδί [prev. work] 281 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; γονάτων ἐλαφρὸν ὁρμάν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 5.20; ἐ. ποδῶν ἴχνι᾽ ἀειράμεναι Callias Epigrammaticus “anonymous fragment” 391; ἐλαφρὰ ἡλικία\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] the age of <b>active</b> youth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.5.27 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐλαφροί, οἱ, <b>light troops</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “An.” 4.2.27 \">Refs</a>] (restricted to cavalry who fight at close quarters, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Asclepiodotus Tacticus “Tact.” 1.3): _metaphorically_, πόλιας θῆκεν ἐλαφροτέρας\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>] made them <b>easier in condition,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" epigram Gr. 905 (from Gortyn). \">Refs</a>] <i>adverb</i> -ρῶς <b>nimbly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 217; ὀρχεῖσθαι πυρρίχην 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 6.1.12. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>light-minded, unsteady, fickle</b>, πᾶν πλῆθός ἐστιν ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 6.56.11 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. λύσσα <b>light-headed</b> madness, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 851. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.b</b></Level4> <b>gentle, mild</b>, σφᾶς αὐτοὺς -οτάτους τοῖς συνοῦσι παρέχοντας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.31, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Epistulae” 360c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>small</b>, ποταμός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 16.17.7 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; <b>of small power</b> or <b>strength</b>, πόλεις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 5.62.6. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> <b>relieved</b> of a burden, ψυχὴ ἐ. καὶ δι᾽ αὑτῆς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 4.3.32. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> Ἐλαφρός· Ζεὺς ἐν Κρήτῃ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1645","accentedUnicode":"ἐλαφρός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1640","matchingForm":"ἐλάσσων","stepTransliteration":"elassōn","gloss":"lesser","_zh_tw_Gloss":"小","_es_Gloss":"menor ","_zh_Gloss":"小"},{"strongNumber":"G1644","matchingForm":"ἐλαφρία","stepTransliteration":"elafria","gloss":"lightness","_zh_tw_Gloss":"輕忽","_es_Gloss":"ligereza","_zh_Gloss":"轻忽"}],"shortDef":"light, not burdensome","mediumDef":"light, not burdensome <br /><b>light, not heavy, not burdensome</b> <ref='Mat.11.30'>Mt. 11:30</ref>; <ref='2Co.4.17'>2Cor. 4:17</ref>*","stepGloss":"light","stepTransliteration":"elafros","count":2,"_es_Definition":"liviano, ligera, fácil de llevar ; leve, insignificante","_zh_tw_Definition":"重量上輕的 (太 11:30; 林後 4:17)","_zh_Definition":"重量上轻的 (太 11:30; 林后 4:17)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"nhẹ; nhẹ nhàng.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"輕微, 輕省","_es_Gloss":"liviano ","_zh_Gloss":"轻微, 轻省"}]}